fields.Title: Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): ""The Return, well... It's part urba..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "The Return, well... It's part urban myth -- part political science. It's a fool's hope, sir, and it's also all I've got." She smiles. "They say there will be an *event*. That it will happen somewhere here..."

fields.Title: Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): ""Don't you know, sir? I thought you..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Don't you know, sir? I thought you were from around here. You look like *Mr. Revachol*."

fields.Title: You: "Why does it rise?"
fields.Dialogue Text: Why does it rise?

fields.Title: Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): ""Something is happening. In this ci..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Something is happening. In this city." She nods -- a puff of smoke. "I can feel it. When I'm out here at night..."

fields.Title: Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): ""So, officer, what were we talking..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "So, officer, what were we talking about -- in the final hours of this twilight world?"

fields.Title: Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): ""Silence, officer. Wouldn't have th..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Silence, officer. Wouldn't have thought you the silent type... What were we talking about?"

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""*Le Retour...*" the lieutenant say..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "*Le Retour...*" the lieutenant says. His forehead furrowed, he puts his notes down.

fields.Title: Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): ""So, superstar law official -- what..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "So, superstar law official -- what were we talking about?"

fields.Title: You: ""Never mind. Tell me something else.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Never mind. Tell me something else."

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""And what would that miracle be?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "And what would that miracle be?"

fields.Title: Conceptualization: "It's an empty vessel, an amphora wa..."
fields.Dialogue Text: It's an empty vessel, an amphora waiting to be filled. Something always *returns* from the past -- it's how the future happens. And when it does, many guesses turn out to have been right.

fields.Title: You: "Revert your eyes to the rooftop and..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Revert your eyes to the rooftop and shudder.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""These streets?" He looks over the..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "These streets?" He looks over the railing. "I'm not so sure, miss."

fields.Title: Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): ""But at the same time, I mean -- th..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "But at the same time, I mean -- things can't go on like this forever. Something will give. It always does."

fields.Title: Jump to: [Shivers: "Her thought trails off. The wind pi..."]
You: ""Oh, you don't know? I drank so muc..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Oh, you don't know? I drank so much I can't remember my entire life. Turns out that can happen to a human being."

fields.Title: Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): ""As I said -- there's talk. In the..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "As I said -- there's talk. In the competitive intelligence crowd. A lot of people, like me, who need... a new colour on the map. It's all blue, you see. And that blue doesn't like us."

fields.Title: You: ""Is this why you said you would lik..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Is this why you said you would like to surrender in a *free* Revachol?"

fields.Title: Inland Empire: "Still, the story influenced her cho..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Still, the story influenced her choice of where to run. It must have some hidden layers...

fields.Title: Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): ""In Revachol. Revachol West. They s..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "In Revachol. Revachol West. They say it will happen soon -- and that it will change everything."

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Don't be so sure." The lieutenant..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Don't be so sure." The lieutenant looks to the sea. "Something is coming -- *trouble*. It will be a hard spring. I don't know what it is, exactly, but..." He shakes his head.

fields.Title: Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): ""I'm waiting for the miracle to hap..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I'm waiting for the miracle to happen. It'll take one to get me out of the mess I'm in."

fields.Title: Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): ""The Return, of course." She smiles..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "The Return, of course." She smiles. "Now, I know I'm not from *around* here -- I would only be hitch-hiking. The Return is a big hit in the industrial espionage circles. A lot of desperate, seedy types there. All screwed in this unipolar world."

fields.Title: You: "For whom?"
fields.Dialogue Text: For whom?

fields.Title: Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): ""I do." She lights another one."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I do." She lights another one.

fields.Title: Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): ""So, officer. Sad silence -- a lame..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "So, officer. Sad silence -- a lamentation? What were we talking about?"

fields.Title: Shivers: "From the vapour, a great cumulus is..."
fields.Dialogue Text: From the vapour, a great cumulus is formed. A cloud castle one thousand metres high. A flock of seagulls screams, hitch-hiking on the thermal. They too are part of the procession, the honour watch.

fields.Title: You: ""You came all this way because of a..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "You came all this way because of a rumour?"

fields.Title: Shivers: "Everyone is a guest on this isola...."
fields.Dialogue Text: Everyone is a guest on this isola. A guest of the air and the water, and the humidity between. You are as well, surely.

fields.Title: You: "What is she waiting for?"
fields.Dialogue Text: What is she waiting for?

fields.Title: Rhetoric: "So she thinks -- at least partly --..."
fields.Dialogue Text: So she thinks -- at least partly -- that this Return will feature a self-governing Revachol. She has already placed her bets.

fields.Title: Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): ""No, I came all this way on a false..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "No, I came all this way on a false passport and some money. To hide, mostly. In the most volatile part of the Rel Belt, where it's easiest to disappear."

fields.Title: You: "Is she safe here?"
fields.Dialogue Text: Is she safe here?

fields.Title: Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): ""You mean here -- in Martinaise?" S..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "You mean here -- in Martinaise?" She takes a drag, slow and long...

fields.Title: Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): ""Of the king? Of the nation? Of com..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Of the king? Of the nation? Of communism? Return on investment?" She tilts her head. "I don't know exactly. It's meant to be vague, as promises generally are."

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""I agree, detective." The lieutenan..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I agree, detective." The lieutenant looks to the sea. "Something is coming -- *trouble*. It will be a hard spring. I don't know what exactly, but..." He shakes his head.

fields.Title: Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): ""So, officer..." the young woman sa..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "So, officer..." the young woman says with a sigh.

fields.Title: Shivers: "As safe as you keep her."
fields.Dialogue Text: As safe as you keep her.

fields.Title: Shivers: "Her thought trails off. The wind pi..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Her thought trails off. The wind picks up again. Above her, a great cumulus cloud rises -- ready to fall down as precipitation. April will come, then May; a month, maybe two from now... you shudder. The feeling dissipates. The thought ends.

fields.Title: Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): ""Sure.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Sure."

fields.Title: You: ""How soon will it happen?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "How soon will it happen?"

fields.Title: Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): ""Something is happening in this cit..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Something is happening in this city." She nods -- a puff of smoke. "I can feel it. When I'm out here at night."

fields.Title: You: ""Thank you -- one last question. Do..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Thank you -- one last question. Do you *really* think it will happen?" (Conclude.)

fields.Title: Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): ""Soon. But it's been *soon* for alm..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Soon. But it's been *soon* for almost half a century now, so don't hold your breath."

fields.Title: Shivers: "Continuously nothing. The sky slowl..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Continuously nothing. The sky slowly slides above you. The young woman exhales, the scent of menthol tobacco. Sounds like a sigh.
fields.Alternate1: The sky slowly slides above you, raining down. The young woman exhales, there's menthol tobacco in the air.
fields.Alternate2: The sky slowly slides above you, snowing down. The young woman exhales, there's menthol tobacco in the snowy air.

fields.Title: You: ""The Return of *what* exactly?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "The Return of *what* exactly?"

fields.Title: You: ""Miss. What are you waiting for?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Miss. What are you waiting for?"

fields.Title: Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): ""The Return, well... It's part urba..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "The Return, well... It's part urban myth -- part political science. It's a fool's hope, sir, and it's also all I've got. They say there will be an *event*. That it will happen somewhere here..." She looks around, then at the sky.

fields.Title: You: ""And what miracle would that be?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "And what miracle would that be?"

fields.Title: You: ""Some political event? How do you k..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Some political event? How do you know of this?"

fields.Title: Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): ""Yeah..." She looks at the sky, the..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Yeah..." She looks at the sky, then at you. "I guess it is."

fields.Title: You: ""I don't.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "I don't."

fields.Title: Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): ""Something is happening -- in this..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Something is happening -- in this city. I can feel it. When I'm out here at night..."

fields.Title: Shivers: "Nothing happens -- there is a mass..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Nothing happens -- there is a mass of droplets above the planetary body, colourless, merging into one another...
fields.Alternate1: Nothing happens -- absolutely nothing. A mass of droplets above the planetary body, colourless, merging into another, raining down on you.
fields.Alternate2: Nothing happens -- absolutely nothing. A mass of droplets above the planetary body, colourless, merging into one another -- scattering snow over the city and the sea.

fields.Title: Shivers: "For Gloria. Soon these clouds will..."
fields.Dialogue Text: For Gloria. Soon these clouds will all fall down as rain. Spring will come. Two more months. Maybe less. It's time.
fields.Alternate1: For Gloria. Soon these clouds will all fall down as even greater rain. Spring will come. Two more months. Maybe less. It's time.

fields.Title: You: ""You know I'm a bit spotty -- about..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "You know I'm a bit spotty -- about a great many *things*. Like being a cop for example."

fields.Title: Jump to: [Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): ""Something is happening. In this ci..."]
Shivers: "The sky is more black than grey; yo..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The sky is more black than grey; you hear the distant murmur of motor-connections somewhere south of here. That is all.

fields.Title: You: "Shudder."
fields.Dialogue Text: Shudder.

fields.Title: Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): ""No need to worry, lieutenant." She..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "No need to worry, lieutenant." She turns to the lieutenant. "I'm sure the streets will not erupt in seditious violence just yet."

fields.Title: Shivers: "For her. The guest. Waiting."
fields.Dialogue Text: For her. The guest. Waiting.

fields.Title: You: "Nod."
fields.Dialogue Text: Nod.

fields.Title: Shivers: "The sky is low and cold. You hear t..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The sky is low and cold. You hear the distant murmur of motor-connections somewhere south of here. That is all.

fields.Title: You: ""What is the Return?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "What is the Return?"

fields.Title: You: ""Humour me.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Humour me."

fields.Title: You: ""So do I.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "So do I."

fields.Title: Shivers: "A warm column of air rises around y..."
fields.Dialogue Text: A warm column of air rises around you, encircling the building you stand on. You feel its twisting shape, bits of paper and birds -- on the *thermal*. Along with several million litres of water. All rising up into the great Insulindian sky.
fields.Alternate1: A warm column of air rises around you -- up to the falling rain -- encircling the building you stand on. You feel its twisting shape, bits of paper and birds on the *thermal*. Along with several million litres of water. All rising back into the great Insulindian sky.
fields.Alternate2: A column of air rises around you, encircling the building you stand on. You feel its twisting shape, bits of paper and birds -- on the *thermal*. Along with several million litres of water as the snow melts on the ground. All rising up into the great Insulindian sky.

fields.Title: Shivers: "Because it's warm -- from the gathe..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Because it's warm -- from the gathering spring; from the oceanic current flowing into the bay; the people on the streets; and the machines that hum in the harbour. Heavy fuel oils too.

fields.Title: Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): ""Where the walls are still porous a..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Where the walls are still porous and you can slip through. This is just... something to get me through the night you know. A little *esprance*."
